verbose_text: The first, the expression of IL-5Ralpha on CD34+ progenitor cells, was examined since there is an increase in the proportion of bone marrow CD34 + progenitor cells expressing IL-5Ralpha 24 hours after allergen challenge in asthmatic subjects [XREF_BIBR], and pretreatment with BUD in vivo partially reduces baseline levels of CD34 + IL-5Ralpha + bone marrow cells, but does not abrogate the allergen induced upregulation [XREF_BIBR].
